com.tomtom.speedtools.domain

Class Uid<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomtom.speedtools.domain.Uid<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class Uid<T>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Generic Unique ID class, immutable. Basically just an abstraction of UUIDs. Used to unique identify... well, anything, really. No 2 Uid objects shall be equal unless they are the same instance of the Uid class or their underlying UUIDs are equal. Note that type parameter T is not actually used by this class. It just serves to model type-safe references in model code. Note also that this class represents UUID as a String internally, to avoid loads of UUID to String conversions all the time. This makes the class considerably faster in use than the regular Uid class.
